By Esther Egbe
Nigeria Judo Federation has selected Two judokas that will represent the country even as the Commonwealth Youth Games commences tomorrow  in Nassau Bahamas
National Daily learnt that the players are  Taiwo Aremo Peter from Ogun State would Compete in 60kilogramme Men category While  Dorathy Kassim from Nasarawa State would Compete in 48kilogramme Women category respectively.
The National Judo coach, Bashir Bassey  who is always leading the Judo delegation to the games .
The Nasarawa State Judo coach told National Daily that the team are in high spirit and are ready to do their best towards making the country proud even as the gmes commence in earnest soon.

			
